Encyclopedia: Ignorance is bliss, as they say. Go ahead, answer the man!
You: "Do you know who this person was, have I told you..."
Nix Gottlieb: "Firewalker? Yes, yes you are. Just don't breathe in the general direction of your fire-feet. Actually, wait..."
You: "It's going great! I feel like it's really helping me with this case!"
Nix Gottlieb: "Great. Have a medal. I have an autopsy to attend to. An autopsy of one Chester McLaine, who died of *fish poisoning*."
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
lazarethcallhub
Nix Gottlieb: "Yup."
Endurance: The money is probably going to some old, oily...
You: "Doc, someone broke my heart."

Nix Gottlieb: "And no, I *don't* want to hear a *political commentary* on the topic. In fact -- I've got work to do. Some idiot has glued his eyelids shut with Cyanoacrylate. It looks like Mack Torson."
You: "No wonder I'm in so much pain. I feel like I've been... damaged."
Nix Gottlieb: "Yes. Probably in more ways than one."
Jump to: [The actual Radio HUB]
Nix Gottlieb: "Great. I have an autopsy to attend to. An autopsy of one Chester McLaine, who died of *fish poisoning*."
You: But why?
Nix Gottlieb: "Yes, there's no end to the misfortunes fate has seen fit to rain upon me."
You: "I decided to stop. Completely. Forever."
Suggestion: Was that a snarl or a suppressed groan? No love for you here.
You: "I'm sorry I've been such a bother to you..."
You: "Good fortune, you mean good fortune, right? You're basking in the floodlight of my glory."
You: "Yes, we live in difficult times. But at least it's over. Almost over, that is..."
Nix Gottlieb: "Look, pal -- getting *pumped and dumped* is not a disease. People live through it all the time. You should be happy for her."
You: "I still *feel* pretty good though. I can probably take a lot of damage."
Nix Gottlieb: "Yes, positive thinking is a well-known cure-all. My suggestion is to exercise a lot."
Nix Gottlieb: "What, you want me to do blood work for you again, tell you just how bad things really are *across the board*? You want another rundown of everything collapsing inside your body?"
You: "I couldn't reach up and grab a tie from a spinning fan without unbearable pain shooting through my arm."
You: "I see your point. Might as well just get back to work."
You: "No, that doesn't sound like something I can handle right now..."

Esprit de Corps: "Only a month later, when I got a chance to properly thank him, did I find out that *he* had no recollection of the event -- that's Gottlieb for ya. In league with some devil, he is, I'm sure of it. Cheers!" The clinking of beer glasses is drowned in group conversation...
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
You: "I feel like you're making fun of me."
Nix Gottlieb: "I'm the most serious person at this station, detective. Now, do you have any *current, pressing* medical problems?"
You: "So you see it too? That my body is to become the last torch in the darkness?"
Nix Gottlieb: "I see third-degree burns and a referral to a plastic surgeon whom you won't be able to afford. But that's in the future. Do you have any *current, pressing* medical problems?"
Nix Gottlieb: "Hard to tell exactly what it was over the phone. Could be a combination of peripheral neuralgia and high blood pressure. Could be that you were having a heart attack..."
You: "Yes. I want the truth!"

Nix Gottlieb: "You want the real, honest-to-god truth? Stop drinking, eat magnesium and vitamin D. Our station is not a retirement home. We don't have the funds to deal with *rock stars* past their prime."
Encyclopedia: You can still be. There's time. Anyway, answer the man.
firewalkerhub
Nix Gottlieb: "Great to hear it. Stop by some time when you're done with your case -- I'll draw some blood, run it through -- let you know how much 'forever' your liver's going to give you."
Nix Gottlieb: "Gottlieb. What is it now?" There's not the slightest hint of wanting to know the answer in that familiar raspy voice.
Nix Gottlieb: "Great! Any other complaints?"
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
Nix Gottlieb: "Do that. I need to go. Some idiot has glued his eyelids shut with Cyanoacrylate. It *looks* like Mack Torson, but it's hard to say because his eyes are swollen..."
Mack Torson: "It's not fucking cryo-actilate... it's super glue, doc."
Endurance: The firewalker cannot die.
Conceptualization: It would be an artistic statement of some kind or another.
Encyclopedia: Yes, especially young people in young countries. Anyway, answer the man.
Logic: Abstinence *could* have immediate positive effects on your health.
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
Authority: There is no surprise in his voice. Only careless superiority.
You: "You're not surprised? Okay. Anything else?"
You: "I'm in a bad way, doc. A real *bad* way."
Nix Gottlieb: "Oh," the man is unpleasantly surprised. "It's you."
Nix Gottlieb: "Then let's get on with it. Clock is ticking."
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
Nix Gottlieb: "For you it probably is. I'm counting on my lungs outliving your liver by a wide margin." He pauses. "Not that that's anything to fÃªte."
Reaction Speed: Was he speaking about his longer life or your shorter one when he said it was no cause for celebration?

Nix Gottlieb: "That's the tiny vessels pulsating from high blood pressure, stupid officer. You might be sustaining permanent damage to your vision as we speak. Not much I can do about it. I'm not an *eye* doctor."
You: "But... what kind of doctor are you then?"
Nix Gottlieb: "From what I can tell, you're just playing into their hands -- disabling yourself from doing any actually useful work. Now, do you have any *current, pressing* medical problems?"
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
Encyclopedia: Uhm... they already are. Anyway, answer the man.
Composure: He sounds very careless about it all. Positively breezy.
Nix Gottlieb: "The busy kind. It's not life-threatening, just annoying. For you. I've got more important things to do here."
"The busy kind. It's not life-threatening, just annoying. For you, that is, what with your reputation as a sharpshooter. Me -- I've got more important things to do."
Jump to: [lazarethcallhub]
Alice: "..."
Pain Threshold: Don't take it personally. There just wasn't any *juice* left in your carton, pal.
You: "Sure, sure -- but can you tell me about myself? As in, who I am?"
Nix Gottlieb: "*Who* you are? You lost your human visage a while back. Now let's get on with it -- I've got more important things to do."
Nix Gottlieb: "...or, actually!" He seems to be positively surprised by the idea. "It could be *both*, given your profile."
You: "So what do I do?"
You: "Wait... both? But that sounds bad."
Electrochemistry: Oh, but speed, sweet speed... It goes so well with alcohol, too...
Electrochemistry: Which reminds me -- when are we finally going to get that speed?
Nix Gottlieb: "What else? I'm not a *brain* doctor. Look on the bright side -- you've got a whole new life now. Use it wisely."
Drama: It's hard to say if he doesn't believe you -- or doesn't care.

Encyclopedia: Young religious people protesting the Seraise government, which they consider to be oppressive. It's also got something to do with the encroaching Occidental influences on the local way of life. You have to *not* like a lot of things to set yourself on fire.
Chester McLaine: "Fucking... I'm not dead, it just hurts, okay?"
You: "I guess that's it for now." [Hang up.]
Nix Gottlieb: "Mhphm." The phone clicks. Suddenly you hear the already familiar voice...
You: "Yes..."
Nix Gottlieb: "Even better! Anything else? I wouldn't worry about that. Officers your age have coronary trouble all the time. Also -- death is a natural part of life."
You: "Yes, it's Firewalker here."
Nix Gottlieb: "...do exactly that. Put yourself out of your misery. Take a deep diaphragmatic breath in and..." You hear an exaggerated inhale and a long exhale on the other end of the line.
Nix Gottlieb: "You must have me confused for a close personal friend... I am not. I am a medical professional -- with a constant *idiot* emergency on my hands."
Esprit de Corps: One needs tending to right now, he thinks, looking around the room. God, these apes...
Alice: "It will take just a moment, officer..."
She seems to hesitate. "Yes, officer, you will be connected in a moment..."
Alice: Her voices fades out into the familiar radio static.
You: "I don't know anything about fate. I just wanted to talk about a medical issue."
Hand/Eye Coordination: It certainly does not help with aiming...
Empathy: You're detecting very little in the way of empathy from Dr. Gottlieb.
Jump to: [You: ""So what do I do?""]
You: "Wait... pumped and dumped?"
Nix Gottlieb: "That's what the guys say, officer. That some chick pumped you -- and then dumped you. Threw you away like an empty juice carton."
Alice: "..."
Nix Gottlieb: You hear a man clearing his throat briskly, then an answer: "Gottlieb. What'd ya want?"
Empathy: Don't flatter yourself -- he's not going to miss you.

"Good. It would be an awful nuisance if your experiments with your blood pressure were to cause permanent damage to your vision. A nuisance to you, that is, on account of you being so proud of your marksmanship."
